<codeline><highlight class="normal">#<sp/>PaBiLegs<sp/>Structure</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">The<sp/>PaBiLegs<sp/>consists<sp/>of<sp/>4<sp/>joints<sp/>and<sp/>8<sp/>motors,<sp/>as<sp/>every<sp/>joint<sp/>is<sp/>moved<sp/>by<sp/>two<sp/>motors<sp/>(one<sp/>in<sp/>each<sp/>direction).<sp/>Angle<sp/>sensors<sp/>are<sp/>built<sp/>into<sp/>each<sp/>joint<sp/>and<sp/>allow<sp/>us<sp/>to<sp/>know<sp/>the<sp/>position<sp/>of<sp/>the<sp/>legs.<sp/>A<sp/>FPGA<sp/>is<sp/>used<sp/>for<sp/>the<sp/>connection<sp/>to<sp/>the<sp/>computer<sp/>and<sp/>communicates<sp/>with<sp/>the<sp/>motors<sp/>and<sp/>joint<sp/>angle<sp/>sensors.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">A<sp/>force<sp/>sensor<sp/>within<sp/>the<sp/>motor<sp/>allows<sp/>to<sp/>see<sp/>how<sp/>tight<sp/>the<sp/>spring<sp/>tensed.<sp/>This<sp/>gives<sp/>an<sp/>insight<sp/>into<sp/>the<sp/>force<sp/>changes<sp/>while<sp/>other<sp/>motors<sp/>are<sp/>actuating.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
